China Media Group (CMG) held the second rehearsal for the 2022 Spring Festival Gala today. The performance from three generations of artists won a round of warm applause from the audience. This year's Spring Festival Gala has a star-studded lineup. The rigorous performance of the older generation of artists adds a heavy cultural atmosphere to the Gala, while the younger generation fully demonstrate the high-spirited youth and vigor of the new era. This year's Spring Festival Gala shows various programs that strive to reflect the development and changes of the times in laughter and spread positive energy on this very important day of the Chinese people. The gala will be aired at 8 p.m. BJT on January 31, 2022, Chinese New Year's Eve. First broadcast in 1983, the four-hour extravaganza is recognized as the world's most-watched TV show. It features a mix of performances ranging from singing and dancing, Chinese comedy in the form of skits and crosstalk, as well as acrobatics and magic shows.